E[x], E[y]
E[xy]
P(x,y) = P(X=x, Y=y)
P(X=x) = \sum p(x,y)
P_{XY}(x,y)=2^{-x-y}\\ P_X(x)=\sum_y 2^{-x}2^{-y}=2^{-x}\\ P_Y(y)=\sum_x 2^{-x}2^{-y}=2^{-y}\\ P_{XY}(x,y)=P_X(x)P_Y(y)
P_X(x)=2^{-x},\ x\ge1
X
Y
E(X)=E(Y)=\sum_{x=1}^{\infty}x2^{-x}=\frac{0.5}{(1-0.5)^2}=2\\ E(XY)=E(X)E(Y)=4
